dct_description_sm: Compiled from the most recent Surveys in the Hydrographic Office, 1877 ; Published at the Admiralty, 15th May 1877, under the Superintendence of Captain F.J. Evans, R.N: C.B. F.R.S. Hydrographer ; Sold by J.D. Potter, Agent for the sale of the Admiralty Charts ; Engraved by Davies & Company.
Depths shown by soundings, relief by hachures and spot heights.
Shows coastal relief, waterways, low water areas, anchorages (highlighted by orange), islands, lights, railways.
